The paper proposes a novel framework for classifying irregularly sampled time series using deep neural networks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and recurrent neural networks (cs.NE) for comparison. Additionally, the paper focuses on healthcare applications, which could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) for analyzing medical records.
